The paper deals with graph separation problems, specifically Multicut and Steiner Orientation, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The use of gadgets in the proof suggests that the paper may also be relevant to Computational Geometry (cs.CG) and Complexity Theory (cs.CC). Finally, the mention of terminal pairs and graph cuts suggests that the paper may also be relevant to Graph Theory (cs.GT).
